{"id":2217,"date":"2021-12-08T09:17:23","date_gmt":"2021-12-08T08:17:23","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/project.gotriple.eu\/?page_id=2217"},"modified":"2022-03-31T09:01:07","modified_gmt":"2022-03-31T07:01:07","slug":"crowdfunding-resources","status":"publish","type":"page","link":"https:\/\/project.gotriple.eu\/crowdfunding-resources\/","title":{"rendered":"Crowdfunding Resources"},"content":{"rendered":"<div id=\"modal-ready\">\n<p>On this page we are compiling a range of resources about crowdfunding, with a special focus on crowdfunding of research projects from the social sciences and humanities (SSH): newspaper articles, scientific studies, how-to manuals and best practice examples.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>If you know of any publications that you think are worth listing here, please send an email to: Sona Arasteh at arasteh[at]maxweberstiftung.de. Help us build this resource collection!<\/p>\n\n\n\n<div style=\"height:33px\" aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"wp-block-spacer\"><\/div>\n\n\n\n<h2 id=\"generic-articles-on-crowdfunding\">Generic articles on crowdfunding<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<ul><li>Brainard, Jeffrey (26 March 2018). Want to crowdfund your science? New study hints at who is successful. Study of 728 Experiment.com campaigns finds women and students tend to do better. In: <em>Science<\/em>. Online: <a href=\"https:\/\/www.science.org\/content\/article\/want-crowdfund-your-science-new-study-hints-who-successful\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">https:\/\/www.science.org\/content\/article\/want-crowdfund-your-science-new-study-hints-who-successful<\/a>&nbsp;<\/li><li>Conroy, Gemma (10 March 2020). Struggling to win grants? Here\u2019s how to crowdfund your research. Making dream projects a reality. In: <em>nature index<\/em>. Online: <a href=\"https:\/\/www.natureindex.com\/news-blog\/how-to-crowdfund-your-research-science-experiment-grant\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">https:\/\/www.natureindex.com\/news-blog\/how-to-crowdfund-your-research-science-experiment-grant<\/a>&nbsp;<\/li><li>Else, Holly (2019). Crowdfunding research flips science\u2019s traditional reward model. In: <em>nature news<\/em>. Online: <a href=\"https:\/\/www.nature.com\/articles\/d41586-019-00104-1\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">https:\/\/www.nature.com\/articles\/d41586-019-00104-1<\/a><\/li><li>Miller, Zack (2019). The Best Platforms for Crowdfunding Science Research. From Researching Physics to Providing Ultrasound. In: <em>The Balance Small Business<\/em>. Online: <a href=\"https:\/\/www.thebalancesmb.com\/top-sites-for-crowdfunding-scientific-research-985238\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">https:\/\/www.thebalancesmb.com\/top-sites-for-crowdfunding-scientific-research-985238<\/a>&nbsp;<\/li><li>UNESCO (2021). UNESCO Recommendation on Open Science. Document code: SC-PCB-SPP\/2021\/OS\/UROS. Online: <a href=\"https:\/\/unesdoc.unesco.org\/ark:\/48223\/pf0000379949.locale=en\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">https:\/\/unesdoc.unesco.org\/ark:\/48223\/pf0000379949.locale=en<\/a> [Crowdfunding is part of the UNESCO recommendations on OpenScience]<\/li><li>Wemakeit Blog: <a href=\"https:\/\/blog.wemakeit.com\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">https:\/\/blog.wemakeit.com\/<\/a><\/li><\/ul>\n\n\n\n<div style=\"height:20px\" aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"wp-block-spacer\"><\/div>\n\n\n\n<h2 id=\"scientific-publications-on-crowdfunding\">Scientific publications on crowdfunding <\/h2>\n\n\n\n<ul><li>English, Rebecca (2014). Rent-a-crowd? Crowdfunding academic research. In: <em>First Monday<\/em>, 19(1). DOI: <a rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" href=\"https:\/\/doi.org\/10.5210\/fm.v19i1.4818\" target=\"_blank\">https:\/\/doi.org\/10.5210\/fm.v19i1.4818<\/a>&nbsp;<\/li><li>Forbes, Paula, Barbot, Laure, Papaki, Eliza, Schramm, Maxi, Kraker, Peter, &amp; De Paoli, Stefano (2021). TRIPLE Deliverable: D3.2 Report on Co-Design of the Innovative and New Services (DRAFT). Zenodo. DOI: <a rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" href=\"https:\/\/doi.org\/10.5281\/zenodo.5660961\" target=\"_blank\">https:\/\/doi.org\/10.5281\/zenodo.5660961<\/a> [including results from the TRIPLE crowdfunding survey]<\/li><li>Sauermann, Henry, Franzoni, Chiara, Shafi, Kourosh (2018). Crowdfunding Scientific Research (Working Paper). <em>National Bureau of Economic Research Working Paper Series<\/em> 24402. DOI: 10.3386\/w24402, <a rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" href=\"https:\/\/www.nber.org\/papers\/w24402\" target=\"_blank\">https:\/\/www.nber.org\/papers\/w24402<\/a>&nbsp;<\/li><li>Sauermann, Henry, Franzoni, Chiara, Shafi, Kourosh (2019). Crowdfunding Scientific Research. Descriptive insights and correlates of funding success. In: <em>PLoS ONE <\/em>14(1): e0208384. DOI: <a rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" href=\"https:\/\/doi.org\/10.1371\/journal.pone.0208384\" target=\"_blank\">https:\/\/doi.org\/10.1371\/journal.pone.0208384<\/a>&nbsp;<\/li><\/ul>\n\n\n\n<div style=\"height:20px\" aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"wp-block-spacer\"><\/div>\n\n\n\n<h2 id=\"resources-from-the-1st-triple-international-conference-nov-2021\">Resources from the 1st TRIPLE International Conference (Nov. 2021)<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<ul><li>Aversano, Aliz\u00e9 (2021). What is crowdfunding? Presentation at the <a rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" href=\"https:\/\/project.gotriple.eu\/triple-international-conference-2021\/\" target=\"_blank\">1st TRIPLE International Conference &#8220;Empowering Discovery in Open Social Sciences and Humanities&#8221; (TRIPLE Conference)<\/a>, virtual event, 22-24 November 2021 (Session 2 (Day 2): Panel \u2014 Is crowdfunding a solution to the lack of research funding for social sciences and humanities?, Part 1). Zenodo. DOI: <a rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" href=\"https:\/\/doi.org\/10.5281\/zenodo.5776320\" target=\"_blank\">https:\/\/doi.org\/10.5281\/zenodo.5776320<\/a><\/li><li>De Paoli, Stefano, Forbes, Paula, Oniga, Andreea (2021). TRIPLE Crowdfunding User Research. Presentation at the <a rel=